The paper deals with the computational complexity of manipulating a randomized rule for the assignment problem, which is a topic in game theory (cs.GT) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The algorithms presented in the paper involve computational techniques such as polynomial-time algorithms and NP-hardness, which are common in the sub-categories of algorithms and data structures (cs.DS), machine learning (cs.LG), and multi-agent systems (cs.MA).
